pr_body:
Refactor `zulip.scss`

**Testing Plan:** <!-- How have you tested? -->
Checked twice with `git bisect` and `rebase` due to a weird issue that made every message invisible. :sweat_smile:
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 428208302, 'comment_body': 'This change is wrong; I applied
```
diff --git a/static/styles/zulip.scss b/static/styles/zulip.scss
index 9852de84ce..2a7f36eaf8 100644
--- a/static/styles/zulip.scss
+++ b/static/styles/zulip.scss
@@ -351,20 +351,20 @@ label {
 
 /* List of text-like input types taken from Bootstrap */
 input {
-    [type="text"],
-    [type="password"],
-    [type="datetime"],
-    [type="datetime-local"],
-    [type="date"],
-    [type="month"],
-    [type="time"],
-    [type="week"],
-    [type="number"],
-    [type="email"],
-    [type="url"],
-    [type="search"],
-    [type="tel"],
-    [type="color"] {
+    &[type="text"],
+    &[type="password"],
+    &[type="datetime"],
+    &[type="datetime-local"],
+    &[type="date"],
+    &[type="month"],
+    &[type="time"],
+    &[type="week"],
+    &[type="number"],
+    &[type="email"],
+    &[type="url"],
+    &[type="search"],
+    &[type="tel"],
+    &[type="color"] {
         font-size: inherit;
         height: 1.4em;
     }
```

to fix it.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 20, 18, 7, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 428215806, 'comment_body': "I think this commit is probably counterproductive, so I skipped it.  These don't really represent a common set of related CSS we want to organize, but instead a set of N unrelated things that happen to all involve divs.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 20, 18, 20, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: WIP subscriptions: Migrate to HTML5 color picker from spectrum.
pr_body:
Earlier Zulip was using `spectrum-colorpicker` which seemed to be an
abandoned project (last commit 3 years ago) and since we have dropped
support for IE11, switching to HTML5 native color picker was right choice.

The following commit removes absolute code referring to
`spectrum-colorpicker` and introduces the support for HTML5 color picker
for changing stream colors. Now user can change stream colors from the
sidebar itself or using streams settings menu using HTML5 native color
picker with an option of using presets that works in all current browsers.

Fixes #14961.

**GIFs or Screenshots:** <!-- If a UI change.  See:
  https://zulip.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/screenshot-and-gif-software.html
  -->

![Sidebar](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23737560/87484400-a8838c00-c653-11ea-8f4d-7130fd886072.gif)

Changing Color From Stream Setting Menu:
![Stream Settings](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23737560/87484414-b0dbc700-c653-11ea-91eb-b640ecf07f7c.gif)

pr_body:
Partially Fixed #3128 

- [ ]  You shouldn't be able to click "Find team" if you don't have a valid list of email addresses. Slack does this really nicely: https://slack.com/signin/find
- [x]  We should send an email regardless of whether they are in a Zulip org or not. 
- [ ]  The followup page should have links to resend the email or enter a different email address. 
- [x]  The URL of the followup page currently has the email as a URL parameter, which should be removed.

**Testing Plan:** <!-- How have you tested? -->
Creating multiple organizations on local workspace and attach a user to multiple user.
Enter multiple email id on /accounts/find page a mix or single org account, multiple org account, email not registered on any org.

pr_title: realm: Add option to list realms publicly.
pr_body:
The following commit adds a feature to allow sponsored realms to be
listed publicly. This is done by adding a field in Realm model and
toggle it via front-end. The feature will disabled by default for the
production, it can be enabled by editing value of `OSS_SHOWCASE` in
`defualt_settings.py`.

Fixes: #15844.

pr_title: nginx: Tweak nginx settings to customize 5xx page.
pr_body:
Tweaked the `nginx.conf` to map error status with their error message and
enabled ssi (server side include) to pass variables to the resulting page.
Included the imports into the `5xx.html` to print error code and it's
message. Tweaked the webpack config to preserve comment in the error page
to preserve the ssi.

Fixes #14611.

**Testing Plan:** <!-- How have you tested? -->
Manually add a location in `puppet/zulip/files/nginx/zulip-include-frontend/app`
to return either 502/503/504 error.
Eg:- 
```
location /test-path.html {
    return 502;
}
```

Or visit my test instance [here](https://majordwarf.zulipdev.org/502/).

**GIFs or Screenshots:** <!-- If a UI change.  See:
  https://zulip.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/screenshot-and-gif-software.html
  -->
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23737560/79893396-a37eba00-8421-11ea-870c-2e11f97d6d91.png)



<!-- Also be sure to make clear, coherent commits:
  https://zulip.readthedocs.io/en/latest/contributing/version-control.html
  -->
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 412512710, 'comment_body': 'Can you explain how this mechanism works?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 21, 21, 44, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 412512821, 'comment_body': '(Maybe with a link to the relevant part of the nginx documentation?)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 21, 21, 44, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 412517207, 'comment_body': "So once we have enabled SSI we can access variables/files from nginx backend. In `nginx.conf` we have mapped status codes with their error message. So we are using status code sent via nginx and printing it's code along with the message.

Here we are using the status code sent via nginx and only reloading the page if it was a 502 error code. Also, why the if condition? It makes no sense to reload the site until and unless it was a bad gateway.

SSI Guide: https://www.cambus.net/nginx-and-server-side-includes/
SSI Documentation: https://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_ssi_module.html", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 21, 21, 52, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'majordwarf', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 412521234, 'comment_body': 'We definitely do not want to enable SSI for everything we serve. This would include user-uploaded content.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 21, 22, 0, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'andersk', 'type': 'User'}]
